
The U.S. Food And Drug Administration (FDA) is searching for the cause of a
salmonella outbreak that it has traced to raw tomatoes. More than 165 people
across the U.S. have become ill with salmonella poisoning since April.
On June 7, the FDA  issued an advisory, warning consumers not to eat several
common types of tomatoes. VOA Producer Barry Unger has more in a report voiced
by Tony Budny.
 
 
